There is another icon that can appear, the grey shield icon ([[File:Perf SafetyBlocked.png|frameless|30x30px]]). This icon appears when viewing a user's preferred fallback avatar is not possible, the default [[Special:MyLanguage/Robot|Robot]] avatar, will be shown instead. Here are the reasons why the icon would appear:
{| class="wikitable"
!Type
!Explanation
|-
|Blocked via Safety
|The user's avatar has been blocked by the [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust and Safety#Managing avatars|Trust and Safety System]].
|-
|Manually Hidden
|The user's avatar has been manually hidden by using the "Hide Avatar" button in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]].
|-
|Loading
|The user's avatar is loading. Either if the avatar is still downloading or initializing.
|}

===Choosing a fallback===
To choose a fallback avatar, open the avatar page on the VRChat website, then select "Use as Fallback" under the Manage Avatar section.

There are 2 options for choosing a fallback:

*Uploading a custom avatar as a fallback.
*Using avatars from the [[Special:MyLanguage/Public Avatars|Public avatar]] row as a fallback.

====Custom fallbacks====
Users can upload their own custom fallback avatar. There are some requirements in order to upload and use a custom fallback:

*Be built for all available platforms.
*Performance rank must be Good{{performance|good|22}} or better on the respective platform.
*Have the Fallback flag set from the Android upload.

==Deprecation==
With the release of [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202522 2025.2.2], VRChat mentioned in the release notes that Fallbacks are being deprecated, cited with the following reason:
<blockquote>
''Fallbacks are being deprecated slowly over time in favor of impostors....''</blockquote>

Fallbacks can still be used and are functional, but are not selectable within the client. Changing fallbacks can only be done from the website.

